CsSnxPb1−xI3 can be assumed to be the combination of CsSnI3 and CsPbI3 with a certain molar ratio. Among the compounds, only CsSnI3 participates in the oxidation reaction. Then, this process can be simplified to22CsSnI3+O2→Cs2SnI6+SnO2.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
